<h3 id="2-2-5">License, Credit, and Distribution</h3>
<img src="~/img/docs/sign.png" class="small-img" />
<p>
	When map makers pour tons of hours into their work, we want to make sure they get the credit they deserve. However, it is important to note the boundaries of LevelImposter's GPLv3 license and how maps should be distributed on their official platforms.
</p>
<p>
	In order to maintain the security of map users, distribution of LevelImposter map files is limited to the exported json file only. This means distribution of the LevelImposter dll files without proper license, credit, and source code is <b>illegal</b>. In order to properly distribute your new map, you can post the exported json file onto LevelImposter's official <a href="https://discord.gg/9jJEBQ4qJs">Discord</a> and <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/LevelImposter/">Reddit</a> or distribute the download link for LevelImposter along with your json file on non-LevelImposter platforms.
</p>
<p>
	Due to these limitations, credit for the original map maker can come in the form of signs and text located inside the map file. This is similar to what you would find in a Gmod map. Signs can be drawn in paint or photoshop then placed beside spawn or wherever else you may like. This ensures credit to the original map maker without the security risks of running unauthorized code.
</p>

